          <article><div class="full-span blue media-center-footer">
<div class="wrapper">
<h3 class="eyebrow">For Journalists</h3>

<h2>Need information, background, comments, or referrals to other sources?</h2>

<p>The National Center for Science Education is the only national organization that specializes in defending the teaching of controversial issues (such as evolution and climate change) in public schools. Because of our special expertise and experience, NCSE is often cotacted by members of the press who are writing about the evolution/creationism controversy, or about the teaching of global warming and other climate science issues that have come under political attack. Our staff can provide reliable information about creationism, evolution, climate change, and the state of science education in the United States.</p>
<a href="mailto:info@ncse.ngo">Get in touch with NCSE</a></div>
</div></article>
    
